<p>I'm using Undertow as <code>WebSocket</code> implementation (as part of Wildfly) and I want my <code>@ClientEndpoint</code> to automatically reconnect on error. As <a href="http://undertow.io/javadoc/1.2.x/io/undertow/websockets/jsr/WebSocketReconnectHandler.html" rel="nofollow">documentation says</a>, it is possible to use <code>WebSocketReconnectHandler</code> to process reconnects, but I can't find any examples of using it without programmatical endpoint deployment.</p>  <p>My endpoint annotated with <code>@ClientEndpoint</code> and I'm using this code to connect to remote server:</p>  <pre><code>try {     WebSocketContainer container = ContainerProvider.getWebSocketContainer();     container.connectToServer(new MyClientEndpoint(), new URI("ws://localhost:8080/myserver/quote")); } catch (Exception e) {     logger.warning(e.getMessage());     throw new RuntimeException(e); } </code></pre>  <p>So, how can I register WebSocketReconnectHandler for this endpoint?</p>